Introduction
At IBM, we know that transformation drives change, and it is in our DNA to continuously transform. Our Federal Consultants help drive large scale change that spans IBM business units and geographies. As a part of this team, you will have the unique opportunity to be a part of driving IBM’s ongoing transformation as a company that continuously innovates and leads the market.

Your Role and Responsibilities
You’re right at the intersection of technology, people, and process, helping your clients transform how they adapt to shifts in the market, and more closely align their business strategy and vision.

Associate Consultants are important and key players for our clients. You’ll be their guide to developing an understanding of their processes, goals and objectives to define their future state, then help them get there.

You’ll help clients understand leading technologies and the impact they can have on traditional business processes. You’ll have an opportunity to build a powerful portfolio of interesting and rewarding experiences, taking advantage of opportunities to master new skills, learning about and becoming an expert in our client’s industries, and tackle new challenges.

Work you could do as an Associate Consultant: Hybrid Cloud:
IBM provides a variety of solutions to clients and our specialized teams serve these needs. As a result, the specific work and technologies vary by the team you may be joining. Below is a list of the types of work Associate Consultants do.
Assist with Cloud migration and system application implementation or upgrades.
Run or support workshops, meetings and stakeholder interviews.
Document requirements from the product owner/business lead.
Develop process maps to understand As-Is and To-Be scenarios.
Translate client requirements into analytical specifications for the implementation of the IBM solution.
Define current and future operational scenarios (processes, models, use cases, plans and solutions) and works with client using an agreed methodology to ensure proper translation of business requirements to solution requirements.
Project business value of a solution in client-relevant terms and drive adoption of key performance indicator (KPI) impact with key client stakeholders.
Develop communications tailored to specific audiences.
Work in an Agile, collaborative environments.
Use IBM’s Design Thinking to help solve client’s challenges.
Analyze data to support conclusions and strategies, and design organization.
Our Hybrid Cloud Associate Consultant opportunities are in one of the following two core skill areas, DevOps Engineering and Full Stack Development/Engineering:

DevOps Engineer – Associate Consultant
The DevOps Engineer engages in a wide variety of cloud migration and cloud adoption projects using the DevOps model.
Works in Agile, collaborative environment to build, deploy, configure, and maintain systems, which may include software installations, updates, and core services
Manage problem identification, system architecture definition, software specification and design, implementation, testing, customer training, and deployment of open source solutions
Works with development teams to enable a continuous integration environment that sustains high productivity levels and emphasizes defect prevention techniques
Support to automate testing and deploy code and monitor
Work in close coordination with the development and operations team such that the application is in line with performance according to the customer’s expectation
Drive corrective and preventive actions to close incidents
Build common tooling to solve problems, automate and ensure problems are not repeated
Full Stack Dev/Engineer – Associate Consultant
Full Stack Developer/Engineers work on solutions across the entire tech stack.
Work with databases, distributed systems, microservices, message bus/queues, and frontend user interfaces.
Develop highly scalable microservices / RESTFUL Services and APIs
Develop user-friendly interfaces and dashboards , translation of designer mockups and wireframes into front end code.
Write unit and integration tests
Document your work Research and implement new technologies to solve customer problems
Experience in Python - Flask, Django, Java - Springs framework, JavaScript - Node JS, Express,
Frontend frameworks - React JS/Angular/Vue.js, container services - Kubernetes.




Required Technical and Professional Expertise
DevOps:
Linux – knowledgeable in Linux – RHEL (Red Hat Enterprise Linux) or similar, Debian or similar, other distributions
Networking – basic understanding of TCP/IP, NAT, DNS
Virtualization – experience in or exposure to using hypervisors
Cloud – knowledge of at least one Cloud Provider (Azure, AWS, Google as examples)
Containers and orchestration – familiar with or experience working with containers (Docker or similar container runtime engines) and orchestration tools (Kubernetes, OpenShift or similar)
Knowledgeable in OpenShift, for examples familiar with differences compared to native Kubernetes or other orchestration solutions on top of Kubernetes

Full Stack:
Experience with one of the following object-orientated programming languages: Java, Python, C++, C, HTML, JavaScript
Exposure to or experience building RESTful APIs and Web Services (i.e., Java, Spring Boot, .NetCore, NodeJS)
Understanding of container-based cloud applications and CI/CD pipeline tools
Exposure to or experience working with UI development (i.e., Angular, React, Node.JS, JavaScript)
All Hybrid Cloud Associates require business consulting skills including:
Can understand clients’ needs and challenges and apply creative and logical approach to identify solutions.
Demonstrate exceptional quantitative analysis skills and ability to derive recommendations informed by data and insights.
Can work on multiple tasks concurrently and meet deadlines, while maintaining focus in an environment with conflicting demands.
Ability to communicate complex situations clearly and simply by listening actively and conveying difficult messages in a positive manner.
Demonstrate strong interpersonal skills with ability to collaborate and work effectively in an intense team environment, able to build direct working relationships across all levels of the IBM and client teams.
Preferred Technical and Professional Expertise

